===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|水|斿|c1=s|c2=p|t1=water|ls=psc}}. However, the phonetic component has a reference to travelling, hence it adds part of the meaning.

===Etymology 1===
From {{der|zh|sit}}. Cognate with {{cog|bo|རྒྱུ་བ||to walk; to wander}}, {{cog|lep|ᰚᰪᰌᰦ|tr=yŭ-da|gloss=to flow}}, {{cog|raw|yø||to flow}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Same word as {{och-l|遊|to roam; to travel}}. Cognate with {{och-l|流|to flow}}, {{och-l|泅}}. Probably unrelated to {{och-l|油|id=1|abundant}}, {{och-l|滺|flowing}}.

